The Federal Road Safety Corps Marshal, Dr. Boboye Oyeyemi, said he received with shock the early morning crash of a tanker leading to inferno in which lives and properties were lost at Felele, a suburb of Lokoja, today 23rd September 2020. According to Bisi Kazeem, Assistant Corps Marshal, Corps Public Education Officer, Federal Road Safety Corps, Oyeyemi said the corps will increase its mobilization of stakeholders in its effort to prevent any recurrence of such unfortunate incident. He further commiserated with the families of those who lost their lives and properties in the said inferno while promising to sustain the recertification and training of tanker drivers.